### 1. Check server is alive
GET http://localhost:3000/

### 2. Create a high priority task
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Build the API",
  "description": "Finish the task manager project",
  "priority": "high"
}

### 3. Create a medium priority task
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Write unit tests",
  "description": "Test all endpoints thoroughly",
  "priority": "medium"
}

### 4. Create a low priority task
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Update documentation",
  "description": "Keep the README up to date",
  "priority": "low"
}

### 5. [FAIL CASE] Missing title (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "This should fail validation"
}

### 6. [FAIL CASE] Missing description (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should also fail"
}

### 7. [FAIL CASE] Invalid priority (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad priority task",
  "description": "This should fail too",
  "priority": "urgent"
}

### 8. Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks

### 9. Filter by high priority
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?priority=high

### 10. Filter by low priority
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?priority=low

### 11. Filter completed tasks
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=true

### 12. Filter pending tasks
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=false

### 13. Get single task (replace ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID

### 14. [FAIL CASE] Get non-existent task (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/99999

### 15. Update task title only (replace ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Build the API (updated)"
}

### 16. Update task priority (replace ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "low"
}

### 17. [FAIL CASE] Update with invalid priority (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "urgent"
}

### 18. Mark task as complete (replace ID)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID/complete

### 19. Filter completed tasks (should now show the completed one)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=true

### 20. Get stats
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/stats

### 21. Upload PDF attachment (replace ID and path)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID/attachment
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< /path/to/your/test.pdf
--boundary--

### 22. [FAIL CASE] Upload non-PDF file (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID/attachment
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

< /path/to/your/test.txt
--boundary--

### 23. Get task to confirm attachment is saved (replace ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID

### 24. Delete a task (replace ID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID

### 25. [FAIL CASE] Get deleted task (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/YOUR_ID

### 26. Get final stats
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks/stats